      "medial_sagittal_midline_structures": "Medial sagittal — midline structures",
      "cut_the_brain_in_half_corpus_callosum_": "Cut the brain in half: corpus callosum, thalamus, hypothalamus, cingulate, hippocampus. The deep structures the lateral view hides — most of the limbic system lives here.",
      "superior_view_top_down": "Superior view — top-down",
      "look_down_at_the_brain_the_longitudina": "Look down at the brain. The longitudinal fissure splits L and R hemispheres; the central sulcus separates motor (front) from somatosensory (back). Asymmetry reveals.",
      "inferior_view_bottom_up": "Inferior view — bottom-up",
      "look_up_from_underneath_cranial_nerves": "Look up from underneath. Cranial nerves I–XII exit here. The Circle of Willis (basilar + vertebral + ICA) supplies the brain — strokes happen at these branch points.",
      "neurotransmitters_chemistry_of_mind": "Neurotransmitters — chemistry of mind",
      "glutamate_excite_gaba_inhibit_dopamine": "Glutamate (excite), GABA (inhibit), dopamine (reward + motor), serotonin (mood + GI), norepinephrine (alertness), acetylcholine (memory + autonomic). Drug targets all live here.",
      "neuron_anatomy_single_cell": "Neuron anatomy — single cell",
      "dendrites_input_soma_axon_output_termi": "Dendrites (input) → soma → axon (output) → terminal. Action potential travels at 10–120 m/s; myelin makes it faster. Synapses can be excitatory or inhibitory.",
      "sleep_stages_n1_n2_n3_rem": "Sleep stages — N1, N2, N3, REM",
      "cycles_every_90_min_n3_deep_for_memory": "Cycles every ~90 min. N3 (deep) for memory consolidation; REM for emotional processing + procedural memory. Adolescents need 8–10 hrs; chronic deprivation impairs everything cognitive.",
      "eeg_waves_brain_rhythms": "EEG waves — brain rhythms",
      "delta_deep_sleep_theta_drowsy_memory_a": "Delta (deep sleep) → Theta (drowsy + memory) → Alpha (relaxed wakefulness) → Beta (active thinking) → Gamma (focused attention). Frequency rises with arousal level.",
      "cross_lateral_wiring_left_vs_right": "Cross-lateral wiring — left vs right",
      "each_hemisphere_controls_the_opposite_": "Each hemisphere controls the OPPOSITE side of the body. Left = language + sequential reasoning (most people); right = spatial + emotional processing. Stroke maps directly here.",
      "search_regions_functions_conditions": "🔍 Search regions, functions, conditions...",
      "search_brain_regions_functions_and_con": "Search brain regions, functions, and conditions",
