      "the_haudenosaunee_iroquois_confederacy": "The Haudenosaunee (Iroquois Confederacy) call these plants De-oh-há-ko — \"they sustain us.\" The Three Sisters are spiritual beings and precious gifts, central to Haudenosaunee language, ceremony, songs, and cosmology. This is not merely a farming technique — it is a living relationship between people and plants.",
