      "rate": "Rate",
      "gate": "Gate",
      "an_arpeggiator_plays_the_notes_of_a_ch": "🔬 An arpeggiator plays the notes of a chord one at a time in sequence. \"Up\" goes low to high, creating ascending energy. \"Down\" descends for a cascading feel. Rate controls speed (lower = faster). Gate controls how long each note rings (100% = legato, 10% = staccato). Try rate=100ms + 4 octaves + up pattern for a classic trance arp!",
      "live_mic_effects_lab": "🎤 Live Mic Effects Lab",
      "sing_speak_or_play_an_instrument_hear_": "Sing, speak, or play an instrument — hear effects in real-time!",
      "monitor_hear_yourself_use_headphones": "🔊 Monitor (hear yourself — use headphones!)",
      "how_effects_change_sound_waves": "🔬 How Effects Change Sound Waves",
      "filter_cutoff": "Filter (Cutoff)",
      "removes_frequencies_above_lowpass_or_b": "Removes frequencies above (lowpass) or below (highpass) a threshold. Like cupping your hand over your mouth — it removes high frequencies, making sound \"darker.\"",
      "delay": "Delay",
      "creates_echoes_by_copying_the_signal_a": "Creates echoes by copying the signal and playing it back after a short time. Feedback controls how many echoes repeat.",
      "reverb_2": "Reverb",
      "simulates_room_acoustics_by_creating_t": "Simulates room acoustics by creating thousands of tiny echoes that blend together. Small room = short reverb, cathedral = long reverb.",
      "distortion": "Distortion",
      "clips_the_waveform_peaks_turning_smoot": "Clips the waveform peaks, turning smooth sine waves into harsh, angular shapes. This adds new harmonics that weren't in the original sound.",
      "chorus": "Chorus",
      "duplicates_the_signal_with_a_slight_co": "Duplicates the signal with a slight, continuously varying delay. This simulates multiple voices/instruments playing together slightly out of time.",
      "tremolo": "Tremolo",
      "rapidly_varies_the_volume_up_and_down_": "Rapidly varies the volume up and down, creating a pulsating effect. Common in surf guitar and organ music.",
      "use_headphones_when_monitoring_to_avoi": "Use headphones when monitoring to avoid feedback loops! The mic routes through all the effects above (filter, delay, reverb, etc.) — adjust them to hear how each one transforms your voice or instrument.",
      "connect_your_microphone_to_run_your_vo": "Connect your microphone to run your voice or instrument through the effects chain in real-time.",
      "see_your_voice_as_a_waveform_frequency": "See your voice as a waveform + frequency spectrum. Hear how filter, delay, reverb, distortion, and chorus physically change sound waves.",
      "xy_performance_pad": "🎯 XY Performance Pad",
      "touch_drag_x_pitch_y_filter_effect": "Touch & drag — X = pitch, Y = filter/effect",
      "xy_pad_performance": "XY Pad Performance",
      "the_xy_pad_maps_your_finger_mouse_posi": "The XY pad maps your finger/mouse position to musical parameters in real-time. The X axis controls pitch (left = low, right = high). The Y axis controls the filter cutoff frequency (top = bright, bottom = dark). This is similar to instruments like the Korg Kaoss Pad, which revolutionized live electronic music performance by turning 2D gestures into sound.",
      "xy_performance_pad_left_right_is_pitch": "XY performance pad. Left–right is pitch, up–down is filter brightness. Use the arrow keys to move and play a note; press Escape or Space to stop.",
