      "real_bridges_are_designed_by_sliding_t": "real bridges are designed by sliding the worst possible vehicle across every point on the span and recording the maximum force in each member. The \"influence line\" of a member is how its force varies with the load's position. Each member has its own worst case — usually NOT in the same place as the worst case for any other member.",
