      "reef_shark": "Reef Shark",
      "visual_hunters_with_electroreceptors_l": "Visual hunters with electroreceptors (Lorenzini ampullae) that detect bioelectric fields of prey. Ink masks visual + chemical trail; sudden jet breaks tracking.",
      "large_shark": "Large Shark",
      "apex_pelagic_predators_giant_pacific_o": "Apex pelagic predators. Giant Pacific octopuses, Humboldt squid, even giant + colossal squid are documented prey. Hard to ink-evade in open water.",
      "moray_eel": "Moray Eel",
      "ambush_hunters_lurking_in_crevices_the": "Ambush hunters lurking in crevices. They smell prey + strike from cover. Hiding in coral doesn't help — that's WHERE the eel is. Octopus must abandon shelter + flee.",
      "bottlenose_dolphin": "Bottlenose Dolphin",
      "active_echolocators_sound_based_hunter": "Active echolocators — sound-based hunters. Ink doesn't hide you from sonar. Pod-hunting + intelligence makes evasion hard. Best response: depth change or rapid jet.",
      "sperm_whale": "Sperm Whale",
      "the_apex_predator_of_giant_colossal_sq": "The apex predator of giant + colossal squid. Sonar penetrates ink + dark water. Sucker scars on sperm whale skin are battle marks. Most cephalopod-vs-whale fights end with the whale.",
      "sea_otter": "Sea Otter",
      "pacific_northwest_specialist_will_pry_": "Pacific Northwest specialist. Will pry octopuses out of dens with their hands + dive repeatedly. Persistent + intelligent — hideouts don't save you for long.",
      "lingcod": "Lingcod",
      "pacific_northwest_ambush_predator_with": "Pacific Northwest ambush predator with huge mouth. Octopuses are routine prey. Lingcod with octopus arms hanging out of their mouths are a common dive photo.",
      "larger_cephalopod": "Larger Cephalopod",
      "cephalopod_cannibalism_is_the_norm_lar": "Cephalopod cannibalism is the norm. Larger common octopus eats smaller common octopus. Humboldt squid pack-hunt smaller squid. Same camouflage tricks don't work — your predator is using them too.",
      "seal_sea_lion": "Seal / Sea Lion",
      "vibrissae_whiskers_detect_water_distur": "Vibrissae (whiskers) detect water disturbance from prey movement — sensing modality octopuses don't typically defend against. Fast + agile in 3D water column.",
      "ink_flee": "Ink + Flee",
      "eject_a_melanin_mucus_pseudomorph_deco": "Eject a melanin + mucus pseudomorph (decoy) + jet sideways. Disrupts visual tracking; the mucus also temporarily disables predator smell. Classic + iconic.",
      "jet_escape": "Jet Escape",
      "explosive_mantle_contraction_siphon_je": "Explosive mantle contraction + siphon-jet for instant linear acceleration. Best at evading pursuit predators or sudden attacks.",
      "camouflage_freeze": "Camouflage + Freeze",
      "best_response_to_a_predator_that_hasn_": "Best response to a predator that hasn't spotted you yet — match the substrate + stop moving. If you're already detected, this fails.",
      "deimatic_display": "Deimatic Display",
      "sudden_high_contrast_display_eyespots_": "Sudden high-contrast display + eyespots + posture extension. Triggers predator startle reflex — buys ~0.5 seconds for the next escape move. Used by cuttlefish + Humboldt squid + others.",
      "arm_autotomy_2": "Arm Autotomy",
      "sacrifice_an_arm_it_detaches_reacts_in": "Sacrifice an arm — it detaches + reacts independently for ~1 hour, distracting the predator. Octopus regrows it in weeks. The cost is real (~12% of total mass + significant neuron loss) but better than dying.",
      "depth_change": "Depth Change",
      "rapidly_descend_or_ascend_in_some_case": "Rapidly descend (or ascend in some cases) to break predator pursuit. Especially squid — they can dive 100+ meters quickly. Effective against surface-bound dolphins + birds.",
      "mimicry_defense": "Mimicry Defense",
      "impersonate_a_venomous_unpalatable_spe": "Impersonate a venomous/unpalatable species (sea snake, lionfish, flatfish). The predator backs off thinking you're dangerous. Mimic octopus specialty.",
      "hideout_den": "Hideout / Den",
      "retreat_into_a_crevice_shell_or_constr": "Retreat into a crevice, shell, or constructed shelter (coconut octopus). Best against visual predators that can't reach into small spaces.",
      "counter_strike_venom": "Counter-Strike (Venom)",
      "blue_ringed_octopus_specialty_signal_a": "Blue-ringed octopus specialty: signal aposematic warning rings + deliver tetrodotoxin if attacked. Most predators learn to avoid blue-ringed individuals after one encounter — or don't survive to learn.",
      "match_downwelling_light_from_above_wit": "Match downwelling light from above with ventral photophores or symbiotic bacterial light organ. Erases your silhouette to predators looking up from below.",
      "your_survival_record": "📊 Your survival record",
      "escapes": "Escapes",
