      "typical_of_relaxed_cruising_speeds_mos": "Typical of relaxed cruising speeds. Most cephalopod swimming happens here.",
      "hovering_fine_maneuver": "Hovering / fine maneuver",
      "gentle_steering_jet_octopuses_spend_mo": "Gentle steering jet. Octopuses spend most of their time at speeds in this range.",
      "the_physics": "⚗️ The physics",
      "bernoulli_s_principle_gives_the_exit_v": "Bernoulli's principle gives the exit velocity of water from the siphon: ",
      "v_jet_2_p": "v_jet = √(2·P/ρ)",
      "where_p_is_mantle_pressure_and_is_seaw": " where P is mantle pressure and ρ is seawater density (1025 kg/m³). Thrust scales with siphon area and jet velocity squared: ",
      "f_a_v": "F = ρ·A·v²",
      "bigger_siphon_more_area_more_thrust_bu": ". Bigger siphon = more area = more thrust, but at the cost of slower jet velocity (Bernoulli is independent of A; thrust IS).",
      "pick_a_species_2": "🦑 Pick a species",
