      "the_strange_biology_of_jet_swimming": "❤️ The strange biology of jet swimming",
      "cephalopods_have": "Cephalopods have ",
      "three_hearts_2": "three hearts",
      "two_branchial_hearts_one_per_gill_and_": " — two branchial hearts (one per gill) and one systemic heart that pumps blood to the body. Here's the weird part: ",
      "the_systemic_heart_stops_beating_durin": "the systemic heart STOPS BEATING during sustained jet swimming",
      "blood_circulation_pauses": ". Blood circulation pauses.",
      "why_jet_swimming_generates_enormous_in": "Why? Jet swimming generates enormous internal pressure during each mantle contraction — high enough to interrupt the systemic heart's pumping cycle. The cephalopod is essentially holding its circulatory breath while it sprints.",
      "this_is_part_of_why_octopuses_prefer": "This is part of why octopuses prefer ",
      "using_their_arms_on_the_substrate_for_": " (using their arms on the substrate) for any distance over a few body-lengths — their circulatory system can't sustain a long jet swim. Squid, with more streamlined bodies + denser muscle, manage longer jet phases but still pay the cost. Humboldt squid pack-hunts feature short sprint pulses interspersed with recovery glides.",
      "otto_2": "Otto",
      "inky_2": "Inky",
