      "the_hard_question": "🤔 The hard question",
      "octopuses_last_shared_a_common_ancesto": "Octopuses last shared a common ancestor with vertebrates about ",
      "600_million_years_ago": "600 million years ago",
      "at_the_level_of_a_flatworm_like_marine": " — at the level of a flatworm-like marine animal with no real brain. Everything cephalopods have built since (camera eyes, problem-solving cognition, possibly subjective experience) evolved ",
      "completely_independently": "completely independently",
      "from_the_path_that_led_to_mammals": " from the path that led to mammals.",
      "if_consciousness_exists_in_octopuses_i": "If consciousness exists in octopuses, it isn't consciousness like ours derived from a shared ancestor. It would be a ",
      "second_independent_evolutionary_instan": "second, independent evolutionary instance of consciousness on Earth",
      "that_has_implications_for_how_we_study": ". That has implications for how we study minds, treat animals, and even how we look for life elsewhere.",
      "the_octopus_is_the_closest_thing_to_an": "\"The octopus is the closest thing to an intelligent alien we may ever meet.\" — Peter Godfrey-Smith, ",
      "other_minds": "Other Minds",
