      "why_this_matters_5": "🎧 Why this matters",
      "the_ocean_is_not_silent_sounds_are_cri": "The ocean is NOT silent. Sounds are critical for many marine species — from whale communication to dolphin echolocation to fish spawning calls. Notably, cephalopods themselves are LARGELY DEAF in the vertebrate sense; they detect particle motion in water rather than pressure waves. This means SOUND is mostly a vertebrate-marine channel.",
